Step 86. Have your Python script produce an Excel file with this table (named exactly CAP Mapping):
CAP IDBU1001Operations1002IT1003Marketing1004unassigned
Step 87. Drop the Excel file into the SharePoint folder watched by the trigger.
Step 88. Go to Power Automate → left sidebar → My flows → click your flow.
Step 89. Click the 28-day run history section (or Run history tab). Within ~30 seconds, a new run appears.
Step 90. Wait for the run to finish (green check = succeeded, red X = failed).
Step 91. Click into the run. If succeeded, go check your main SP list. Expected end state:
CAPIDBU1001Operations (updated)1002IT (unchanged)1003Marketing (new)1004(blank — unassigned)9999(gone — deleted)

If It Fails
In the run history, click the failed run → find the red-X action → click to expand → look at Inputs, Outputs, and the error message.
Common errors and what they mean:

"The expression is invalid" — typo in an expression. Compare letter-by-letter against this guide.
"Field 'CAPID' not found" — SP column internal name doesn't match. Verify.
"Table 'CAP Mapping' not found in file" — Python isn't naming the table correctly, file isn't .xlsx, or table name has a typo.
"Invalid lookup value" — the BU Id expression isn't producing a number, or it's writing to the wrong field. Check whether the action UI shows BU or BU Id.
All rows look "new" and existing rows got deleted — usually a space mismatch: 'CAP ID' (Excel header, with space) vs 'CAPID' (SP internal name, no space). Check actions 39, 44, and 71.

To report back: paste the exact error text and which named action failed. I'll diagnose.

Summary
You've built:

Trigger — fires when file lands in SharePoint folder
Get_feed_rows — reads the Excel table
Get_current_SP_items — snapshot of main SP list before changes
Get_BU_List — snapshot of lookup source list
Loop_feed_rows_upsert — for each Excel row:

Find matching SP item (if any)
Find BU lookup ID (if any — blank if unassigned or not in BU_List)
If match → Update; if no match → Create


Loop_SP_items_reconcile — for each original SP item:

If CAP ID no longer in feed → Delete



Total: ~9 actions plus branches. Build it, test it, report back. 🚀
